\begin_layout Section
Lagrangian Encodes Objective and Constraints
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First some shorthand: If 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\in\reals^{d}$
\end_inset

, we write 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\succeq0$
\end_inset

 as a shorthand for 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}\ge0$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,\ldots,d$
\end_inset

.
 Similary, if 
\begin_inset Formula $c\in\reals^{d}$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\succeq c$
\end_inset

 is shorthand for 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda-c\succeq0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We claim that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sup_{\lambda\succeq0}\left(f(x)+\lambda g(x)\right)=\begin{cases}
f(x) & \mbox{for }g(x)\le0\\
\infty & \mbox{otherwise.}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Exercise
Convince yourself that this is true.
 (Hint: Find the sup when 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x)\le0$
\end_inset

 and when 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x)>0$
\end_inset

.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Exercise
Show that the following optimization problems are equivalent:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\textrm{minimize} &  & f(x)\\
\textrm{subject to} &  & g(x)\le0
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

is equivalent to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\inf_{x}\left(\sup_{\lambda\succeq0}\left(f(x)+\lambda g(x)\right)\right).
\]

\end_inset

Hint/Solution: Based on the previous exerise, if 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x)>0$
\end_inset

 (i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

not feasible
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for the first optimization problem), then 
\begin_inset Formula $\sup_{\lambda\succeq0}\left(f(x)+\lambda g(x)\right)=\infty$
\end_inset

.
 So the infimum of the second optimization problem will not occur at any
 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x)>0$
\end_inset

.
 Thus the following problem is equivalent to the second problem:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\inf_{\left\{ x\mid g(x)\le0\right\} }\left(\sup_{\lambda\succeq0}\left(f(x)+\lambda g(x)\right)\right).
\]

\end_inset

But when 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x)\le0$
\end_inset

, we know from the previous exercise that the supremum evalutes to 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)$
\end_inset

.
 Thus the second optimization problem is also equivalent to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\inf_{\left\{ x\mid g(x)\le0\right\} }f(x),
\]

\end_inset

and this is exactly the first optimization problem.
 
